  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because of the fact that Dr. de Sousa Mendes ignored the orders of the Portuguese government-- disobeyed the orders, as a matter of fact-- the Portuguese government then sent the ambassador of Portugal in Spain to Bordeaux, France, which was the closest, and they retrieved Dr. de Sousa Mendes from his position.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I guess at one point in time, they ran out of the visas shortly before the ambassador of Spain came in and you wrote visas on playing pieces of paper stating that my name is so and so and so, I am the-- the-- consul of Portugal here and-- in Bordeaux, France, and allow these people-- permit these people to pass through into Portugal.",
      "word_count": 65
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I guess one of the places was-- that they passed through was in Irun, in the north-- north border between Spain and France.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "At one point in time, the-- some of the-- several areas of the border in the southern part of France had been closed by the Germans in agreement with-- with the Spanish government.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But ultimately, Dr. de Sousa Mendes, some statistics refer to the fact that he probably saved over 30,000 lives, of which well over 10,000 Jewish lives and many others.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Many, many predominant people passed through to his grace.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Interesting enough is that Dr. de Sousa Mendes and his family, they had 14 children.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were devout Catholics from the north of Portugal.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "However, Dr. de Sousa Mendes' family in 1497, they were Jews.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were forced to convert to Christianity.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So they became the so-called crypto-Jews, if you wish at times referred to as Muranos.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And so I'm certain that-- that he knew about it.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
